spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: CoreRISC-V_AXI4 is based on SiFive's E31 Coreplex advanced RISC-V core built by SiFive, Inc. CoreRISC-V_AXI4 supports the RV32IM architecture, with a 32-bit datapath and implementing the I(Base Integer) and M (Integer Multiply and Divide) extensions. This CoreRISC-V_AXI4 also contains: - 8kB instruction cache, - 8kB data cache, - PLIC (programmable interrupt controller), - JTAG debug interface. The coreplex interfaces with the external system via two AXI4 compliant master buses, one for memory accesses and one for memory-mapped I/O accesses.
